typedef matrix<double, 11, 11> sample_type;

using net_type = loss_multiclass_log<
	fc<2,
	relu<fc<64,
	max_pool<2, 2, 2, 2, incept_b<
	max_pool<2, 2, 2, 2, incept_a<
	input<sample_type>
	>>>>>>>>;
*/


If I start to change network architecture (below) and start to use 2x2 and 3x3 convolutions in block_a2 and block_a3 (instead of 3x3 and 5x5), then the tool starts to crash.
